Al Habtoor Leighton Wins $109 Million Contract For Headquarters

-- B y   Z a i n a b   F a t t a h
-- 
2011-04-04T05:55:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/al-habtoor-leighton-wins-109-million-contract-for-headquarters.html
Al Habtoor Leighton Group, the
company that’s building the Paris Sorbonne University campus in
Abu Dhabi, has been awarded a 400 million dirham ($109 million)
contract to build a new headquarters for  Abu Dhabi Islamic Bank. (ADIB)   Construction of the two towers will start “immediately”
and is set to be completed within 18 months, the company said in
an e-mailed statement today. The towers will include 12 upper
floors, ground floor and mezzanine level as well as four levels
of basement parking.  Al Habtoor Leighton Group is a joint venture, formed in
2007, between Al Habtoor Group and  Leighton Holdings Ltd. (LEI)  of
Australia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zainab Fattah in Dubai on 
 zfattah@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net . 